pr_review_body:
@themurtazanazir thanks for the updates.

This leaves the V2 of the API disconnected from the implementation on V1. We would need to add the same parameters on the V2 (code pointers [here](https://github.com/pytorch/vision/blob/main/torchvision/prototype/transforms/functional/_misc.py#L85) and [here](https://github.com/pytorch/vision/blob/main/torchvision/prototype/transforms/_misc.py#L115)).

@vfdev-5 Any concerns/feedback about the nature of this extension?

I did not review `colorbynone2` so I am not sure if my comment is found on a proper ground but having a listener attached to a data structure this way (given two way binding) feels a bit unfortunate.

There were few things you've considered but did you consider having a module level singleton dispatcher object that you use to subscribe and unsubscribe?

```ts
// dispatcher.ts

type EventKey = string;
const listeners: Map<EventKey, Function> = new Map();

export function addListener(type: string, fn: Function) {
  ...
}

export function dispatch(type: string) {
  ...
}
```

@tonybaloney Thanks for the PR! :tada: 

I also prefer to import each type from `typing`, but I would like to maintain consistency between modules. :kissing: 

Would you mind checking my suggestions? It also solves the CI.

@tonybaloney Thanks for the PR! :tada: 

I also prefer to import each type from `typing`, but I would like to maintain consistency between modules. :kissing: 

Would you mind checking my suggestions? It also solves the CI.

After one hour of my life spent reviewing this code, this is my feedback:
- Switching from `'` to `"` is noisy. I don't really care, but it might have been easier to review is split in a dedicated commit;
- black provides some improvements in a few places, I agree with the pattern for multi-line interpolation (putting the `% (...)` on the second line instead of having the `%` at the end of the first line);
- It isn't able to put trailing commas in place, which is incompatible with my understanding (and factory_boy's flavour) of PEP8;
- It makes logging calls much nosier, whereas they should be kept compact in order to avoid breaking the reading flow of the program.

Unless we can address at least those two points (trailing commas, logging calls), I don't see the point of going through the hassle of migrating to black.
